Country star Jason Aldean's tour bus struck and killed a pedestrian in the early hours of Monday while it was traveling along a stretch of rural road in Indiana.

Albert Kennedy was hit by the bus at around 1.30am in Knox County according to the local sheriff.

Mr Kennedy, from Vincennes, 'walked out into the middle of the road', according to police and into the path of the bus which was traveling in the northbound lane of US 41 North.

